<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE HOCHMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 KURT REMEMBERED: Courtney Love is paying tribute to her late husband, Kurt 
Cobain, in the upcoming video for her band Hole's song "Doll Parts," casting a 
slight, blond boy to play the young Kurt.  
</P>
<P>
 In the video, directed by Samuel Bay, who also did Nirvana's breakthrough 
"Smells Like Teen Spirit," Love will be seen singing on a big, ornate bed while 
the boy darts in and out of shadows surrounding the scene.Thoughout, Love tries 
to reach to the boy, but he remains elusive. At the end, though, she finally 
makes contact and cradles him in her arms. 
</P>
<P>
 A source close to the project says there had been some initial concern that 
the imagery would be exploitative of Cobain's suicide, but that the results are 
in fact quite "touching." STEVE HOCHMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
