<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW RELEASES; IN BRIEF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Don Snowden Albums are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars 
(fair), three stars (good, recommended), four stars (excellent). 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * * * 1/2, James Newton, "Suite for Frida Kahlo," Audioquest. Perennial 
poll-winning flutist Newton emphasizes his compositional side on his first 
release in four years.The title suite, inspired by four of the famed Mexican 
artist's paintings, creates absorbing mood swings by blending the tone colors 
of an unusual eight-piece ensemble (flute, trombones, bassoon, reeds and rhythm 
section) with occasional dashes of jazz swing and tempo shifts a la Mingus. 
Elsewhere, Newton doesn't neglect his playing, soaring and swooping over the 
changes on the ballad "The Price of Everything" or engaging trombonist George 
Lewis in some formidable free improvising in "Elliptical."Don Snowden Albums 
are rated on a scale of one star (poor), two stars (fair), three stars (good, 
recommended), four stars (excellent). 
</P>
</TEXT>
