<HEADLINE>
<P>
ON LOVE, MARRIAGE AND CATHOLICISM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Well, that mean ol' Catholic Church is at it again ("They Say Love Conquers 
All -- Will It Now?" Aug. 8). Imagine -- trying to uphold their standards 
regarding such little ol' things as marriage and Catholic education.The nerve 
of them. 
</P>
<P>
 Gosh -- to think that he likes rock and she likes the Chicago Bulls. After 
all, he wooed her with "corny lines" and they spend their evenings planted in 
"a spongy green couch playing video games, betting quarters on cards." That 
surely demonstrates that Jennifer, age 17, and Caesar, age 25, have mastered 
what The Times regards as the requirements of marriage. 
</P>
<P>
 And those mean ol' priests. Just look at Father Gregory Coiro. I mean, he's 
"sober robed" and a "big, ruddy-faced man with a serious gaze." Well, who you 
gonna trust, anyhow -- someone like that? I mean Father Coiro must be right out 
of Charles Dickens. 
</P>
<P>
 My God -- what tripe. Try writing that about the Jewish or Islamic faiths. I 
dare you. 
</P>
<P>
 JEREMIAH J. FLANIGAN 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach 
</P>
