<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: CRENSHAW / HYDE PARK; TOXIC-WASTE CLEANUP GOES DOOR-TO-DOOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ERIN J. AUBRY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city Bureau of Sanitation is operating its Mobile Hazardous Household 
Waste program in the Crenshaw/Hyde Park area Thursday through Saturday, going 
door to door to collect potentially hazardous waste materials. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Hazmobile" will allow residents to safely dispose of toxic wastes such as 
household cleaners, auto products and batteries, pesticides, herbicides, paint 
products and old medicines. 
</P>
<P>
 Residents must call the sanitation bureau at 1-(800)-98-TOXIC to make an 
appointment for pickup. 
</P>
<P>
 Councilwoman Ruth Galanter, whose 6th District includes Hyde Park and the 
south Crenshaw area, said she encourages constituents to comb their garages, 
cupboards and medicine cabinets for hazardous materials.  
</P>
<P>
 "Too often, toxic waste goes into our sewer, storm drain system and 
landfills," she said. "We have to protect our families as well as our 
environment." ERIN J. AUBRY 
</P>
</TEXT>
