<P>
GARDENER'S CHECKLIST: GARDENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 For dedicated gardeners, here are suggestions from the California Assn. of 
Nurserymen on what to do in the garden this week:  
</P>
<P>
 * Prepare the garden for winter vegetables by removing all spent summer 
vegetables. 
</P>
<P>
 * For larger blooms from chrysanthemums this fall, dis-bud them now. Also 
stake and tie the plants to prevent drooping and breaking. 
</P>
<P>
 * Plant early flowering sweet peas for an abundance of flowers during the 
holidays. 
</P>
<P>
 * Treat Walnut husk fly with applications of Malathion and spreader sticker. 
</P>
