<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENVIRONMENT: NOTES ABOUT YOUR SURROUNDINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Canyon Classroom: The Oak Canyon Nature Center is offering a guided twilight 
hike Wednesday at 7 p.m. Participants should wear sturdy shoes and bring 
drinking water. At 7:30 p.m., a representative from Orange County Vector 
Control will give a presentation on what outdoor campers and hikers need to 
know about ticks.The program is free. 
</P>
<P>
 The nature center has an interpretive center and natural history museum. 
Canyon hiking trails are open to the public from 9 a.m. to 5 p.m. daily. There 
is no cost for hiking or parking on site. Group tours can be arranged through 
the center. 
</P>
<P>
 To get to the Oak Canyon Nature Center from the Riverside Freeway, go south on 
the Imperial Highway. Take Nohl Ranch Road east about 2 1/2 miles, then turn 
left onto Walnut Canyon Road. The nature center is south of the Anaheim Hills 
Golf Course. For more information, call (714) 998-8380. 
</P>
