<HEADLINE>
<P>
MISSISSIPPI STUDENT WINS WESTERN STATES GOLF EVENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SEAN WATERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hugh Smith of Jackson State College in Mississippi took first place in the 
14th annual Western States Golf Assn.Junior Championships on Aug. 12 at the 
Chester Washington course. 
</P>
<P>
 Smith had a two-day total of 142 to win the college men's division. 
</P>
<P>
 Nakia Whitaker of Southern University won the college women's division with a 
167. 
</P>
<P>
 The two-day tournament was played on three courses: ages 13-18 played at 
Chester Washington; ages 11-12 played at Westchester and ages 7-10 at Jesse 
Owens par-three course. 
</P>
<P>
 In the boys' 7 and 8 division, Austin Sawyer of Los Angeles won with an 
18-hole total of 80 and Veronia Green of West Los Angeles shot 112 to win the 
girls' division. SEAN WATERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA082194-0200 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 071868 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
August 21, 1994, Sunday, Home Edition 
</P>
