</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Israeli soldiers disguised as Arabs fatally shot a Palestinian in the occupied 
West Bank on Saturday, witnesses said. 
</P>
<P>
 A Palestinian photographer for Reuters was among at least eight Arabs wounded 
in the violence. 
</P>
<P>
 Photographer Khaled Zaghari, shot in the left shoulder on his 23rd birthday, 
said undercover soldiers waded into a crowd of stone-throwers and opened fire 
with pistols at close range in the town of Ramallah, just north of Jerusalem. 
</P>
<P>
 It was unclear what touched off the anti-Israeli protest, a regular feature of 
the Palestinian uprising that began in late 1987. 
</P>
<P>
 Zaghari said he was shot while trying to take cover in a shop. 
</P>
<P>
