<P>
KLAN PLANS PROTESTS AT ABORTION CLINICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ku Klux Klansmen plan to demonstrate at abortion clinics in Pensacola within 
the next month, a spokesman for the group said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 The group plans to picket against abortion and the use of federal marshals to 
guard the clinics. 
</P>
<P>
 "I really see no purpose it (using marshals) serves except to intimidate," 
said John Baumgardner, a klan member and former leader, or grand dragon, of the 
Invisible Empire of the Knights of the Ku Klux Klan. No date was set for the 
Pensacola protest. 
</P>
<P>
 The klan participated in anti-abortion protests at a clinic in Melbourne, 
Fla., on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 A patient attending a gynecological appointment at the Aware Woman Center for 
Choice had to pass eight hooded klan members. 
</P>
<P>
 Phyllis Erwin, the clinic's defense coordinator, said she had sent her 
volunteer patient escorts home because abortions were not scheduled and the 
anti-abortion protesters were controlled by police. 
