<P>
COLLEGE FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; AROUND THE NATION; FLORIDA ATOP ANOTHER POLL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Florida Gators, No. 3 in their own state for the past decade, are now No. 
1 in the nation in yet another poll. 
</P>
<P>
 Long overshadowed by Florida State and Miami, the Gators are the preseason 
pick as college football's top team in the Associated Press poll. Florida was 
picked No. 1 Friday in the USA TODAY/CNN poll. 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA was 14th and USC was 17th. 
</P>
<P>
 Florida (1,416 points) edged Notre Dame by two points, the narrowest margin 
since the preseason poll began in 1950. 
</P>
