<P>
WHY SEND BABES? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Why on earth do you repeatedly send "Babes in the Woods" (Weekend Escape, July 
31)? No, I'm not referring to the fact that you covered an all-female camping 
trip. I'm referring to the fact that once again you have sent complete novices 
to write about the forest. 
</P>
<P>
 Why not send writers who enjoy the wilderness? Your writers have trekked to 
Yosemite, Mineral King National Park and Idyllwild, all great locations to 
relax and commune with nature. Yet, every report was filled with complaints 
about things that come with the territory, things like sweat and dirt. Anyone 
who leaves the beauty and tranquillity of Yosemite and can't even drive home 
without stopping for a shower and room service in a $238.71 hotel room, should 
be assigned to write the Scottsdale resort review instead. 
</P>
<P>
 BARBARA SWOVELIN 
</P>
<P>
 Rancho La Costa 
