<HEADLINE>
<P>
22 DROWN WHEN BOAT CAPSIZES IN W. INDIA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A boat on a tour of a flooded river in western India capsized, killing 22 
people, including 14 schoolchildren. 
</P>
<P>
 The news agency Press Trust of India said Saturday that the accident occurred 
Friday on the Chulbandh River in the western state of Maharashtra, about 625 
miles south of New Delhi. Most rivers in India are overflowing their banks 
after the monthlong monsoon rains. 
</P>
