COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; MERCHANT STABBED TO DEATH IN ROBBERY TRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Canoga Park man who operated a local convenience store was stabbed to death 
in Port Hueneme late Friday during a botched robbery, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mohineer Bassi, 42, was stabbed several times in the chest and stomach at the 
B-Mart on East Pleasant Valley Road about 9:30 p.m. Friday, a Port Hueneme 
Police Department spokeswoman said.Bassi, described by a neighboring merchant 
as an employee of B-Mart, staggered next door to the Jester Room Bar, where an 
ambulance was called, the spokeswoman said.  
</P>
<P>
 Bassi was taken to St. John's Regional Medical Center in Oxnard, where he died 
in surgery, a Ventura County coroner's office spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Following leads gathered at the scene, Port Hueneme homicide detectives 
arrested Adolfo Carrillo, 32, of Port Hueneme early Saturday on suspicion of 
killing Bassi, the police spokeswoman said. SCOTT HADLY 
