<HEADLINE>
<P>
POLICE DETONATE SYLMAR PIPE BOMB 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A pipe bomb was detonated by the Los Angeles Police Department bomb squad 
early Friday morning after it was found in a residential neighborhood in 
Sylmar, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The 4-inch bomb -- made out of PVC pipe with caps on both ends -- was found by 
a resident of the 12000 block of Bradley Avenue about 6 a.m., police 
said.Neither the resident's name nor the exact location of the bomb was 
released by authorities. 
</P>
<P>
 "They evacuated the whole block for a few hours," said Officer Sandra 
Castello, adding that the pipe bomb was then taken and destroyed by the bomb 
squad. 
</P>
<P>
 Nobody was injured, police said. There are no suspects or motive in the case, 
and the investigation is continuing. 
</P>
<P>
 "There have been a string of these bombs being found in our division," said 
Lt. Joe Hiltner of the LAPD's Foothill Division. "This is just the latest." 
</P>
