<HEADLINE>
<P>
CALIFORNIA CORNER; FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 SAN LUIS OBISPO -- The 12th annual Central Coast Wine Festival pays tribute to 
the area's wines with tastings and a live auction in downtown's Mission Plaza, 
noon-4 p.m. Sept. 3. Between bids and sips, enjoy food prepared by local chefs, 
live entertainment and arts and crafts.$25. Proceeds benefit the Central Coast 
Region of the Arthritis Foundation. (800) 549-3153. 
</P>
<P>
 SANTA BARBARA -- Spend Labor Day weekend at the sixth annual Santa Barbara 
International Jazz Festival, Sept. 3-5 on West Beach at Stearn's Wharf. Music 
starts at noon daily, concluding at 10 p.m. Saturday-Sunday and dusk on Monday. 
Artists include the Susie Hanson Band and saxophonist Sonya Jason. Also 
featured: "A Taste of Jazz" mini-food festival. $5 per day or $10 for all 
three. VIP seating: $20 per day; $40 for all three. (310) 452-5056. 
</P>
<P>
 HEALDSBURG -- The scenic Healdsburg Plaza is the setting for the Healdsburg 
Antiques Fair on Sept. 4. About 100 vendors are expected. 9 a.m.-5 p.m. Free. 
(707) 433-4315. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN DIEGO -- A large and lively potpourri of music awaits at the 11th annual 
San Diego Street Scene, Sept. 9-10. Seventy-five acts will perform on 13 stages 
in 21 blocks of the downtown Gaslamp Quarter. Wine tasting and international 
foods also featured. 5 p.m.-midnight Friday; 4 p.m.-midnight Saturday. $22 in 
advance; $25 at the door; $39 for both nights (in advance only). (619) 
268-9025. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN JOSE -- Celebrate Mexican Independence Day at the Fiestas Patrias, 10 
a.m.-5 p.m. Sept. 11. Highlights include entertainment, arts and crafts, and 
food, all along Almaden Boulevard, between San Carlos and Santa Clara streets, 
downtown. A parade starts at 10 a.m. on Santa Clara Street at 10th. Free. (408) 
258-0663. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
