<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: A MUSEUM JUST FOR 'VETTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The grand opening of the new National Corvette Museum in Bowling Green, Ky., 
is set for Sept. 2-5. The 68,000-square-foot museum is next to the General 
Motors Corvette Plant, the only facility that builds Corvettes and which draws 
about 70,000 visitors a year. Attractions at the new $15-million museum will 
include a miniature design center, an interactive "Performance Area" and a 
library. 
