<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS: MAPPING MOSCOW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Russian Information Services has come up with the "New Moscow City Map and 
Guide." The updated second edition reflects more than 500 street, feature and 
other changes -- as names revert to pre-revolutionary days, government 
ministries are shuffled around and new embassies open. The map is $6.95 in 
local bookstores, or can be ordered by calling (800) 639-4301. 
</P>
</TEXT>
